properties.value: Barbarians are attackable NPCs found in the Barbarian Village and Outpost. They are commonly fought for training by lower level players due to their low Defence and the many obstacles in the Barbarian Village usable as Safespot. If the player chooses to talk to them, they will taunt the player with quotes such as "Wanna fight?" or "You come to fight, ja?" and immediately attack; players can avoid this by immediately exiting the dialogue instead of clicking to continue.

Barbarians are attackable NPCs found in the Barbarian Village and Outpost. They are commonly fought for training by lower level players due to their low Defence and the many obstacles in the Barbarian Village usable as Safespot. If the player chooses to talk to them, they will taunt the player with quotes such as "Wanna fight?" or "You come to fight, ja?" and immediately attack; players can avoid this by immediately exiting the dialogue instead of clicking to continue.

Gunthor the brave, a unique barbarian, is the strongest barbarian found in the village at level 29. Level 132 Lost barbarian and Confused barbarian variants can be found within the Ancient Cavern.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • The current unique Barbarian NPCs replaced two historical NPCs named Barbarian and Barbarian woman, the former of which is still present in the game files.
  • Some barbarians can be seen in more than one location. Alberich, Fafner, Fasolt, Siegfried, Minarch, Brunnhilde, and Edelschwarz can be found in both the Barbarian Village and the Barbarian Outpost, even though Siegfried's examine states him to be a guard in the Barbarian Village.
    • Similarly, Acelin, Adelino, Aitan, Gutrune, and Sieglinde could be found in both the Barbarian Village and the Barbarian Camp, with Acelin's examine having the same oversight. However they were replaced by unique Barbarians with the release of A Kingdom Divided.
  • Barbarians may ask ""You come to fight, ja?"", with ja meaning "yes" in Scandinavian languages, referencing the barbarians being inspired by Vikings.

'''Barbarians''' are attackable NPCs found in the [[Barbarian Village]] and [[Barbarian Outpost|Outpost]]. They are commonly fought for training by lower level players due to their low Defence and the many obstacles in the Barbarian Village usable as [[safespots|Safespot]]. If the player chooses to talk to them, they will taunt the player with quotes such as "Wanna fight?" or "You come to fight, ja?" and immediately attack; players can avoid this by immediately exiting the dialogue instead of clicking to continue.

[[Gunthor the brave]], a unique barbarian, is the strongest barbarian found in the village at level 29. Level 132 [[Lost barbarian]] and [[Confused barbarian]] variants can be found within the [[Ancient Cavern]].

==Trivia==
*The current unique Barbarian NPCs replaced two historical NPCs named [[Barbarian (historical)|Barbarian]] and [[Barbarian woman (historical)|Barbarian woman]], the former of which is still present in the game files.
*Some barbarians can be seen in more than one location. Alberich, Fafner, Fasolt, Siegfried, Minarch, Brunnhilde, and Edelschwarz can be found in both the [[Barbarian Village]] and the [[Barbarian Outpost]], even though Siegfried's examine states him to be a guard in the Barbarian Village.
**Similarly, Acelin, Adelino, Aitan, Gutrune, and Sieglinde could be found in both the [[Barbarian Village]] and the [[Barbarian Camp]], with Acelin's examine having the same oversight. However they were replaced by [[Barbarian (Barbarian Camp)|unique Barbarians]] with the release of [[A Kingdom Divided]].
*Barbarians may ask "''"You come to fight, ja?"''", with ''[[wiktionary:ja|ja]]'' meaning "yes" in Scandinavian<!-- and other Germanic --> languages, referencing the barbarians being inspired by Vikings.

{{Barbarian Village}}
